td.p:
This request for a preliminary ruling concerns the interpretation of Article 2(1)(c) of Council Directive 75/363/EEC of 16 June 1975 concerning the coordination of provisions laid down by law, regulation or administrative action in respect of activities of doctors (
OJ 1975 L 167, p. 14
), as amended by Council Directive 82/76/EEC of 26 January 1982 (
OJ 1982 L 43, p. 21
) (‘Directive 75/363’), and of Article 45 TFEU as well.

Directive 75/363 was repealed on 15 April 1993 by Council Directive 93/16/EEC of 5 April 1993 to facilitate the free movement of doctors and the mutual recognition of their diplomas, certificates and other evidence of formal qualifications (
OJ 1993 L 165, p. 1
). The latter was repealed by Directive 2005/36/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 7 September 2005 on the recognition of professional qualifications (
OJ 2005 L 255, p. 22
), with effect from 20 October 2007.
